The paper introduces a new logic, PLDL, which extends Linear Dynamic Logic (LDL) to include temporal operators with parameters. The paper focuses on the theoretical aspects of the logic, including a translation of PLDL formulas into non-deterministic B\""uchi word automata and tight upper and lower bounds on optimal parameter values. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL), and Programming Languages (cs.PL).
